@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

@{MS "Introduction"}

SnoopRouter is a tool that is required when creating drivers for hardware that is currently only
supported by PC, MAC or other systems.@{par}

By using SnoopRouter its possible to get an serial protocol within seconds and your job is only to
write the driver by using this log file.@{par}

An example: It took about 4 to 5 hours to get the full serial protocol of the DexDrive for my
@{"MCControl" link "OtherPrgs"}! By using SnoopRouter this took only 30 Seconds. (Booting windows
not included)@{par}

Mice, Graphic tablets, cameras, mobiles, calculators, satellite receivers, or what ever is out
there. Serial hardware is loosing all its transfer secrets within seconds.@{par}

The idea and the creation of this software came on the Amclust party 1/2000! Someone required an
Driver for his digital camera and Mice said: "Guido, do it!". By using the mental and helpful
support of Hulk and the consume of coke and the chocolate bars we created this universal serial
snoop software, which also allows to scan XPRZ-Transfers and/or to connect systems with different
baud rates!

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

@{MS "System requirements"}

SnoopRouter (should work) works on all Amigas with OS 2.0 or higher! Also required are two serial
ports and an null modem cable.@{par}

In addition its required to have at least one device to snoop and an computer/other device that is
able to communicate with this device.@{par}

That`s all!

@endnode
